description:
The ultimate showdown with Norman Osborn and the Dark Avengers is here! Asgard is invaded, and an Avenger dies! The saga that will change the face of the Marvel Universe begins now – don’t you dare miss ‘Siege’!

100 Page special, with starts Siege in the Collector Editions.

Includes material reprinted from Siege #1-2 and New Avengers #61-62.
name: A New Epic SIEGE Begins Here

description:
The ‘Siege’ saga explodes! Asgard faces its greatest challenge as the Avengers battle the Dark Avengers! Captain America takes on the Iron Patriot! Thor clashes with the Sentry! Iron Man is reborn! Don’t miss the shocks!

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #63, Dark Avengers #15 and Siege #3.
name: Earth's Mightiest Heroes Reunited At Last!

description:
In the ruins of Asgard, the Avengers make their last stand against the unstoppable Void – and if they fail, the world is doomed! Find out who survives the final chapter of ‘Siege’!

Includes material reprinted from Siege #4, New Avengers #64 and Age of Heroes #1

The Dark Avengers have been captured, but are they going to stay that way? The Avengers clash with their evil counterparts!

Also: The Hood and Madame Masque are on the run, but the Secret Avengers are hot on their trail – don’t miss an awesome battle with Count Nefaria!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Avengers #16 and New Avengers: Finale #1.

Don’t miss a 100-page special! A five-issue epic saga begins: ‘Second Coming’! Hope and Cable return to the present, and mutantkind’s enemies are waiting for them! The ultimate battle has arrived for the X-Men – and not all of them will survive it! Guest-starring X-Force and the New Mutants!

Includes material reprinted from X-Men: Second Coming #1, Uncanny X-Men #523, New Mutants #12, Nation X #1 and Nation X #3.
name: A New X-Men Epic Begins... Second Coming!

description:
One of the momentous Marvel events begins! Steve Rogers’ closest friends and allies may have found a way to bring back the original Captain America. Or is what they found something more sinister? The Red Skull’s greatest plan to destroy Captain America has been in motion and its completion is almost at hand. Will Captain America be lost forever or will he be ‘Reborn’?

Plus, ‘Siege’ tie-in!! Asgard comes under Siege! As the evil eye of Norman Osborn falls on Asgard, what happens to neighbouring Broxton, Oklahoma? What unexpected enemies will be drawn to the scene like carrion to a carcass? And what unlikely heroes will rise to the town’s defense? The Asgardians face the battle of their immortal lives… and the showdown that’s coming may end their new life on Earth as quickly as it began!

Also, Tony's flight for freedom goes international! Pepper Potts: Prisoner of H.A.M.M.E.R.! And things get very bad for Maria Hill deep in the heart of Texas! As Tony struggles to keep the Silver Centurion armour up and running, Norman Osborn's noose tightens around his neck – every freak and fiend in his rogues gallery is gunning for him – and Madame Masque gets the keys to the kingdom!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Reborn #1, Thor #607 and Invincible Iron Man #13! 76 pages! £2.95!
name: Captain America Reborn!

description:
The race for Steve Rogers is on! On one side - Bucky and the Black Widow and members of the Avengers and Fantastic Four! On the other - Norman Osborn and H.A.M.M.E.R., the Red Skull and his evil hordes, with Doctor Doom waiting in the wings! And where... oh where, is the real Captain America?

Plus, ‘Siege’ tie-in!! War has often come to Asgard before…but never like this! As the Shining City suffers the most brutal earthly attacks in its history, Thor and his allies fight to stay alive and save what they can! Might be a lost cause…

Also, Tony's failing health makes the Iron Man too complicated to pilot. Maria Hill hunts the world's most un-huntable man. Pepper Potts defies Norman Osborn and H.A.M.M.E.R. itself. And all of Iron Man's rogues' gallery is after him and the billion-dollar bounty on his head… starting with the murderous Madame Masque!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Reborn #2, Thor #608 and Invincible Iron Man #14!

Dr. Doom and the Red Skull together again! And what is the fate of the original Captain America, Steve Rogers — and how can he help save himself from the accidental trap he's found himself in? All this and more — as the Avengers and the FF battle insane odds to save Marvel's Fallen Son!

Plus, ‘Siege’ tie-in!! Asgard falls and the Asgrdians are fighting for their very lives against Norman Osborn’s army of super-villains! And what of Loki, the power behind Osborn’s throne? How will Balder react to Loki’s base betrayal?!!

Also, Tony's failing health makes the Iron Man too complicated to pilot. Maria Hill hunts the world's most un-huntable man. Pepper Potts defies Norman Osborn and H.A.M.M.E.R. itself. And all of Iron Man's rogues' gallery is after him and the billion-dollar bounty on his head… starting with the murderous Madame Masque!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Reborn #3, Thor #609 and Invincible Iron Man #15!
name: The Last Stand of Asgard!

description:
Dr. Doom and the Red Skull together again! And what is the fate of the original Captain America, Steve Rogers -- and how can he help save himself from the accidental trap he's found himself in? All this and more -- as the Avengers and the FF battle insane odds to save Marvel's Fallen Son!

Plus, ‘Siege’ tie-in!! The Siege brings Ragnarok to Asgard! The Shining City of Thor and his brothers in arms faces destruction on the greatest scale it’s ever suffered, at the hands of Norman Osborn and his Dark Avengers. But the Norse heroes have bigger problems, when Thor fights Thor! The evil Thor clone has come to kill the God of Thunder and take his place. Even if Asgard survives the Siege…will Thor survive Ragnarok?!!

Also, Tony and Pepper, trapped in Tunguska by Madame Masque, play the ultimate game of truth or dare at the business end of a very loaded gun. Is Tony strong enough and smart enough to escape the clutches of a woman who burns to see him suffer? And halfway around the world, the Black Widow joins Maria Hill, and they summon the most good of all the good guys... Captain America! But is he willing to come to Tony's aid?

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Reborn #4, Thor #610 and Invincible Iron Man #16!
name: Thor Versus Ragnarok!

description: Mitsuomi and Maya are now rivals, but once they were close friends. Their lives were changed forever because of one person: Shin Natsume, Maya’s older brother and Mitsuomi’s mentor. Inheritor of the Dragon Eyes and leader of the Supreme Warrior Faction, the charismatic Shin also bears dark and terrible secrets. Struggling under the burden of the immense power he possesses, and manipulated by those who seek to use that power, Shin begins to lose control. Maya and Mitsuomi each have their own ideas for how to deal with his increasingly erratic behavior, but it’s up to Bunshichi to really beat some sense into him!
name: Vol. 3

description:
In this volume:

A disaffected boy searches for something to put a spark in his tedious life...and finds a manga that puts the fear of the devil in him.

A guy and girl can't find anything they have in common--until they discover a mutual love of a certain gender-bending martial arts manga.

After a schlubby nerd loses his cool at the handsome manga freaks at Kingyo, a classic horror manga teaches him that beauty is only skin deep.

Natsuki's search for her missing mother takes her to a manga museum that has special meaning for her parents.

Someone is setting fire to used bookstores, and Kingyo may be next--unless two mismatched manga fans can stop the arsonist!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 22: Devil Power
  • Chapter 23: A Man Ahead of His Time
  • Chapter 24: A Common Language
  • Chapter 25: Beautiful People
  • Chapter 26: The Kingyo Diaries (The Shiogama Episode)
  • Chapter 27: An Odd Couple
  • Chapter 28: Tomorrow's Visitor
  • A 21st Century Gift (Bonus Manga)
name: Vol. 4

description:
Florence Nightingale

(1820–1910)

British nurse who made tremendous contributions to the modern nursing system. Received her nursing education in Germany before serving as chief nurse in a London hospital. Drafted into military service during the Crimean War, Nightingale strove to improve sanitation amid the wretched conditions of the military field hospital she managed. Also recognized as a pioneering statistician for her tireless compilation of statistical materials. During her military service, her beneficence and dedication to her hospital rounds at night earned her the nicknames “the Lady with the Lamp” and “the Angel of the Crimea.”

Chapters Nineteen to Twenty-Four.
name: Vol. 4

description: “Archie Loves Veronica”: It’s Halloween so Veronica gets into the swing of things by hosting a spook-tacular bash at the Lodge Estate to celebrate and everyone’s invited! Everyone, that is, except for her estranged husband Archie. Left to fend for himself, Archie takes a trip down Memory Lane examining his life with Ronnie and imagining another with Betty. The night’s only getting started as things take a turn for the weird with Archie catching a glimpse of events that could have been and others that never were! The madcap adventure continues in “Archie Loves Betty” as Archie’s universe is turned upside down upon catching sight of Mr. Lodge conducting a secret rendezvous with… Mr. Lodge?! And who is the masked stranger who seems to be guiding this evening’s events? Discover the answers here as mysteries are revealed in this groundbreaking cross-over event that’s only just getting started!

After several exhibits at the Monster Museum are revealed to be bogus, Archie and the gang are commissioned with the task of bailing out the floundering business by hunting down authentic artifacts with investigations leading to witchcraft, a ghost ship and more! Plus, in 'Romantic Times!' by trading stories with an elderly couple, Archie and Betty discover what true love is all about.
name: Saving the Monster Museum / Romantic Times

description:
Presenting two action-packed Mass Effect stories, both written by Mass Effect 3 lead writer Mac Walters! Originally available only from MySpace Dark Horse Presents and USA Today, these peeks into different corners of the Mass Effect universe are now collected together for the special price of just $0.99! In "Incursion," Mass Effect: Invasion's Aria faces an attack on Omega from the Collectors, and in "Inquisition," the Citadel's Captain Bailey is tasked to uncover a traitor in the council's midst!

Written by Mac Walters, lead writer of Mass Effect 3!

Reveals key moments from the Mass Effect saga!

This one-shot collection is exclusive to the Dark Horse Digital Store!
name: Incursion/Inquisition
